		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />グレムリン <em>Gremlin</em> in that logo looks dangerously close to グレムリソ <em>Gremliso</em>. In katakana, where does ン <em>n</em> become ソ <em>so</em> and ソ <em>so</em> become リ <em>ri</em>?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
